Statements: the function of autophagy is not always clear. for instance, studies have shown that inhibition of pi3k and mtor has a cytostatic, but not a cytotoxic effect, both in vitro and in vivo [67]. because autophagy is negatively regulated by the pi3k-akt-mtor pathway, interference with this pathway promotes autophagy. while pharmacologic and genetic inhibition of autophagy along with inhibition of pi3k-akt-mtor pathway resulted in apoptosis, this does not necessarily mean that autophagy was functionally cytoprotective since the cells were actually arrested, presumably through the promotion of autophagy [9].
